.SH SHCrossPowerLC
Compute the cross\-power of two complex functions for a single spherical
harmonic degree.
.SH Usage
\f[CR]cpower\f[R] = SHCrossPowerLC (\f[CR]cilm1\f[R], \f[CR]cilm2\f[R],
\f[CR]l\f[R])
.SH Parameters
.TP
\f[CR]cpower\f[R] : output, complex(dp)
Cross power of the two complex functions for spherical harmonic degree
\f[CR]l\f[R].
.TP
\f[CR]cilm1\f[R] : input, complex(dp), dimension (2, \f[CR]lmaxin1\f[R]+1, \f[CR]lmaxin1\f[R]+1)
The first complex function expressed in complex spherical harmonics.
.TP
\f[CR]cilm2\f[R] : input, complex(dp), dimension (2, \f[CR]lmaxin2\f[R]+1, \f[CR]lmaxin2\f[R]+1)
The second complex function expressed in complex spherical harmonics.
.TP
\f[CR]l\f[R] : input, integer(int32)
The spherical harmonic degree.
This must be less than or equal to the minimum of \f[CR]lmaxin1\f[R] and
\f[CR]lmaxin2\f[R].
.SH Description
\f[CR]SHCrossPowerLC\f[R] will calculate the spectral cross\-power of
two complex functions expressed in complex 4\-pi normalized spherical
harmonics for a single spherical harmonic degree \f[CR]l\f[R].
This is calculated as:
.PP
\f[CR]cpower = Sum_{i=1}\(ha2 Sum_{m=0}\(hal cilm1(i, l+1, m+1) * conjg[cilm2(i, l+1, m+1)]\f[R].
